(1, 'Frontend Developer', 'TechCorp', 'New York, USA', 'Frontend Developer at TechCorp, you will play a key role in building responsive and user-friendly web applications that enhance user experience and engagement. By applying your expertise in frontend technologies, UI/UX design principles, and performance optimization, you will help develop intuitive interfaces that drive business success. You will collaborate with designers, backend developers, and product managers to create visually appealing and high-performance web applications. You will use modern frameworks, responsive design techniques, and frontend best practices to deliver seamless and accessible digital experiences. You will influence frontend development strategies, contribute to design system improvements, and optimize applications for speed and usability. By joining TechCorp, you will become part of an innovative development team committed to delivering high-quality digital solutions.\r\n\r\nUser interface development and optimization: You will develop interactive and engaging user interfaces, ensuring responsiveness and accessibility across devices.\r\n\r\nPerformance and usability: You will optimize frontend code for speed and efficiency, ensuring smooth and intuitive user experiences.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and innovation: You won’t just write code—you will work closely with designers and backend developers to create cohesive and scalable web applications.\r\n\r\nFrontend Developer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and maintain responsive web applications using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and modern frontend frameworks (React, Angular, Vue.js)\r\nEnsure optimal performance and cross-browser compatibility of web applications\r\nCollaborate with designers and backend developers to implement UI/UX designs effectively\r\nOptimize frontend performance through best practices and code efficiency improvements\r\nTroubleshoot and debug frontend issues to enhance user experience\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Web Development, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in frontend development, UI/UX implementation, and performance optimization\r\nProficiency in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and frontend frameworks such as React, Angular, or Vue.js\r\nExperience with version control systems (Git) and build tools (Webpack, Babel)\r\nStrong understanding of responsive design and cross-browser compatibility\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with frontend testing frameworks (Jest, Cypress)\r\nFamiliarity with UI/UX design tools (Figma, Adobe XD)\r\nKnowledge of accessibility standards (WCAG)\r\n\r\nAbout TechCorp\r\nTechCorp is a fast-growing technology company specializing in web development and digital solutions. Our frontend developers play a crucial role in creating engaging and user-friendly web applications for clients worldwide.\r\n\r\n$80,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. TechCorp offers competitive benefits, including remote work options, career development programs, and wellness initiatives.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nTechCorp is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '80,000', '2025-03-05 03:44:36', 'General'),
(2, 'Backend Developer', 'CodeWorks', 'San Francisco, USA', 'Backend Developer at CodeWorks, you will be responsible for developing and maintaining scalable, high-performance server-side applications that power innovative digital solutions. By leveraging your expertise in backend technologies, database management, and API development, you will ensure seamless data processing and system integration. You will collaborate with frontend developers, product managers, and DevOps teams to create robust and secure backend architectures. You will use modern programming languages, cloud services, and microservices best practices to build scalable applications. You will influence backend development strategies, contribute to system optimization efforts, and ensure the reliability of software solutions. By joining CodeWorks, you will become part of a dynamic development team committed to building cutting-edge applications.\r\n\r\nSystem architecture and backend development: You will design, build, and maintain scalable backend services and APIs that support frontend applications and business logic.\r\n\r\nDatabase management and optimization: You will manage relational and NoSQL databases, ensuring efficient data storage, retrieval, and security.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and innovation: You won’t just write code—you will work closely with cross-functional teams to develop reliable and high-performance software solutions.\r\n\r\nBackend Developer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and maintain backend services and APIs using programming languages such as Python, Java, or Node.js\r\nDesign and optimize database structures, ensuring efficient data processing and security\r\nImplement authentication, authorization, and data encryption for secure applications\r\nCollaborate with frontend developers to integrate UI components with backend functionality\r\nMonitor and optimize system performance to ensure scalability and reliability\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in backend development and API design\r\nProficiency in backend programming languages such as Python, Java, or Node.js\r\nExperience with databases (SQL, NoSQL) and cloud services (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud)\r\nStrong understanding of RESTful APIs, microservices architecture, and security best practices\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes)\r\nKnowledge of CI/CD pipelines and DevOps best practices\r\nFamiliarity with GraphQL and message queue systems (Kafka, RabbitMQ)\r\n\r\nAbout CodeWorks\r\nCodeWorks is a leading software development company focused on creating innovative digital solutions for businesses worldwide. Our backend developers play a crucial role in building and optimizing scalable applications.\r\n\r\n$95,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. CodeWorks offers competitive benefits, including professional development programs and remote work options.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nCodeWorks is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '95,000', '2025-03-05 03:44:36', 'General'),
(3, 'UI/UX Designer', 'DesignHub', 'Los Angeles, USA', 'UI/UX Designer at DesignHub, you will play a key role in creating intuitive, visually appealing, and user-friendly digital experiences. By leveraging your expertise in user-centered design principles, wireframing, and prototyping, you will help shape the look and feel of web and mobile applications. You will collaborate closely with product managers, developers, and stakeholders to design engaging interfaces that enhance usability and customer satisfaction. You will use design thinking methodologies, modern design tools, and usability testing to refine user experiences. You will influence design strategies, contribute to brand consistency, and advocate for accessibility and inclusive design. By joining DesignHub, you will become part of a creative team dedicated to delivering exceptional user experiences.\r\n\r\nUser research and design strategy: You will conduct user research, create personas, and design user flows to improve product usability and engagement.\r\n\r\nWireframing and prototyping: You will develop wireframes, prototypes, and high-fidelity UI designs to guide product development.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and innovation: You won’t just design interfaces—you will work closely with developers and product teams to bring user-centric ideas to life.\r\n\r\nUI/UX Designer Responsibilities\r\nCreate user-centered designs through wireframes, prototypes, and mockups\r\nConduct user research and usability testing to refine design concepts\r\nCollaborate with product managers and developers to implement designs effectively\r\nEnsure consistency in branding and design elements across digital platforms\r\nAdvocate for accessibility and inclusive design practices\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Design, Human-Computer Interaction, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in UI/UX design for web and mobile applications\r\nProficiency in design tools such as Figma, Sketch, or Adobe XD\r\nStrong understanding of user-centered design principles and usability testing\r\nExperience with HTML, CSS, and frontend frameworks is a plus\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with motion graphics and animation tools\r\nFamiliarity with design systems and component libraries\r\nKnowledge of accessibility standards (WCAG)\r\n\r\nAbout DesignHub\r\nDesignHub is a leading design agency specializing in UI/UX solutions for startups and enterprises. Our designers play a key role in shaping digital experiences that enhance user satisfaction and business success.\r\n\r\n$70,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. DesignHub offers competitive benefits, including professional development programs and remote work flexibility.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nDesignHub is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '70,000', '2025-03-05 03:44:36', 'General'),
(4, 'Project Manager', 'BizSolutions', 'Chicago, USA', 'Project Manager at BizSolutions, you will lead and oversee the planning, execution, and successful delivery of projects that drive business growth and operational efficiency. By leveraging your expertise in project management methodologies, resource allocation, and stakeholder communication, you will ensure projects are completed on time, within scope, and on budget. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams, clients, and executives to define project goals, mitigate risks, and optimize workflows. You will use Agile, Scrum, and other methodologies to enhance team productivity and deliver high-quality results. You will influence project strategies, contribute to process improvements, and drive innovation in business solutions. By joining BizSolutions, you will become part of a results-driven team dedicated to delivering impactful projects.\r\n\r\nProject planning and execution: You will define project scope, create timelines, allocate resources, and ensure milestones are met.\r\n\r\nRisk management and problem-solving: You will identify potential challenges, develop contingency plans, and proactively resolve project roadblocks.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and leadership: You won’t just manage projects—you will inspire and coordinate teams to achieve successful outcomes.\r\n\r\nProject Manager Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and execute project plans, ensuring alignment with business objectives\r\nCoordinate with cross-functional teams and stakeholders to drive project success\r\nMonitor project progress, identify risks, and implement solutions to keep projects on track\r\nEnsure project deliverables meet quality standards and business expectations\r\nOptimize workflows and introduce process improvements to enhance efficiency\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Project Management, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in project management or business operations\r\nProficiency in project management tools such as Jira, Asana, or Trello\r\nStrong organizational and leadership skills with the ability to multitask effectively\r\nExcellent communication and problem-solving abilities\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nPMP or Scrum Master certification\r\nExperience managing Agile and Waterfall projects\r\nKnowledge of business process optimization and change management\r\n\r\nAbout BizSolutions\r\nBizSolutions is a business consulting and project management firm specializing in helping companies streamline operations and drive innovation. Our project managers play a key role in leading successful initiatives that create lasting business impact.\r\n\r\n$85,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. BizSolutions offers competitive benefits, including leadership training, career development programs, and wellness initiatives.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nBizSolutions is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '85,000', '2025-03-05 03:44:36', 'General'),
(5, 'Data Analyst', 'DataGen', 'Austin, USA', 'Data Analyst at DataGen, you will play a crucial role in analyzing and interpreting complex datasets to drive data-driven decision-making. By leveraging your expertise in statistical analysis, data visualization, and business intelligence tools, you will help uncover insights that optimize business performance and strategy. You will collaborate with stakeholders across departments to identify key metrics, monitor trends, and develop actionable reports. You will use SQL, Python, and data visualization platforms to transform raw data into meaningful insights. You will influence data strategies, contribute to predictive modeling efforts, and support the development of analytical frameworks. By joining DataGen, you will become part of a data-driven team dedicated to delivering impactful insights.\r\n\r\nData analysis and reporting: You will analyze large datasets, identify trends, and generate reports to support business decisions.\r\n\r\nPredictive modeling and insights: You will develop data models, perform statistical analysis, and provide recommendations for business optimization.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and problem-solving: You won’t just analyze numbers—you will work with cross-functional teams to turn data into strategic actions.\r\n\r\nData Analyst Responsibilities\r\nExtract, clean, and analyze large datasets to uncover business insights\r\nDevelop dashboards and reports using BI tools like Tableau or Power BI\r\nIdentify key performance indicators (KPIs) and track business trends\r\nCollaborate with teams to provide data-driven recommendations and support decision-making\r\nEnsure data accuracy, consistency, and security in reporting\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Statistics, Data Science, Computer Science, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in data analysis, reporting, or business intelligence\r\nProficiency in SQL, Python, or R for data querying and analysis\r\nExperience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Looker\r\nStrong problem-solving skills and attention to detail\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience in predictive analytics and machine learning models\r\nFamiliarity with cloud-based data platforms (AWS, Google Cloud, Azure)\r\nKnowledge of A/B testing methodologies\r\n\r\nAbout DataGen\r\nDataGen is a data analytics company that helps businesses make informed decisions through advanced data analysis and insights. Our data analysts play a critical role in transforming data into actionable intelligence.\r\n\r\n$75,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. DataGen offers competitive benefits, including career growth opportunities, mentorship programs, and remote work options.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nDataGen is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '75,000', '2025-03-05 03:44:36', 'General'),
(6, 'DevOps Engineer', 'SecureTech', 'Seattle, USA', 'DevOps Engineer at SecureTech, you will play a critical role in ensuring the reliability, scalability, and security of cloud infrastructure and deployment pipelines. By applying your expertise in automation, configuration management, and CI/CD practices, you will streamline software development and deployment processes. You will collaborate with development and operations teams to implement best practices in cloud architecture, monitoring, and security. You will use containerization, infrastructure as code, and cloud services to optimize system performance and reliability. You will influence DevOps strategies, contribute to security improvements, and drive automation initiatives. By joining SecureTech, you will become part of a cutting-edge team dedicated to building resilient and efficient technology solutions.\r\n\r\nInfrastructure automation and cloud management: You will design, deploy, and maintain scalable cloud infrastructure and automated deployment pipelines.\r\n\r\nMonitoring and security: You will implement monitoring solutions and security best practices to ensure system reliability and compliance.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and problem-solving: You won’t just maintain systems—you will work closely with developers and IT teams to improve deployment workflows and infrastructure performance.\r\n\r\nDevOps Engineer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and maintain CI/CD pipelines for automated software deployment\r\nManage cloud infrastructure using AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud services\r\nImplement monitoring tools like Prometheus, Grafana, or ELK Stack to track system performance\r\nOptimize system reliability, scalability, and security using infrastructure as code (Terraform, Ansible)\r\nTroubleshoot deployment and infrastructure issues to ensure minimal downtime\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in DevOps, cloud infrastructure, or system administration\r\nProficiency in scripting languages like Bash, Python, or PowerShell\r\nExperience with CI/CD tools like Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD, or CircleCI\r\nKnowledge of containerization and orchestration (Docker, Kubernetes)\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nAWS Certified DevOps Engineer or equivalent certification\r\nExperience with security best practices and compliance frameworks (ISO, SOC, HIPAA)\r\nFamiliarity with log management and monitoring tools\r\n\r\nAbout SecureTech\r\nSecureTech is a cybersecurity and infrastructure solutions company dedicated to building secure and scalable cloud environments. Our DevOps engineers play a key role in enhancing automation, security, and system efficiency.\r\n\r\n$105,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. SecureTech offers competitive benefits, including remote work opportunities, security training, and professional development programs.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nSecureTech is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '105,000', '2025-03-05 03:44:36', 'General'),
(9, 'Data Scientist', 'Meta', 'New York, USA', 'As a Data Scientist at Meta, you will shape the future of people-facing and business-facing products we build across our entire family of applications (Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, WhatsApp, Oculus). By applying your technical skills, analytical mindset, and product intuition to one of the richest data sets in the world, you will help define the experiences we build for billions of people and hundreds of millions of businesses around the world. You will collaborate on a wide array of product and business problems with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Product, Engineering, Research, Data Engineering, Marketing, Sales, Finance and others. You will use data and analysis to identify and solve product development\'s biggest challenges. You will influence product strategy and investment decisions with data, be focused on impact, and collaborate with other teams. By joining Meta, you will become part of a world-class analytics community dedicated to skill development and career growth in analytics and beyond.\r\n\r\nProduct leadership: You will use data to shape product development, quantify new opportunities, identify upcoming challenges, and ensure the products we build bring value to people, businesses, and Meta. You will help your partner teams prioritize what to build, set goals, and understand their product\'s ecosystem.\r\n\r\nAnalytics: You will guide teams using data and insights. You will focus on developing hypotheses and employ a diverse toolkit of rigorous analytical approaches, different methodologies, frameworks, and technical approaches to test them.\r\n\r\nCommunication and influence: You won\'t simply present data, but tell data-driven stories. You will convince and influence your partners using clear insights and recommendations. You will build credibility through structure and clarity, and be a trusted strategic partner.\r\nData Scientist, Product Analytics Responsibilities\r\nWork with large and complex data sets to solve a wide array of challenging problems using different analytical and statistical approaches\r\nApply technical expertise with quantitative analysis, experimentation, data mining, and the presentation of data to develop strategies for our products that serve billions of people and hundreds of millions of businesses\r\nIdentify and measure success of product efforts through goal setting, forecasting, and monitoring of key product metrics to understand trends\r\nDefine, understand, and test opportunities and levers to improve the product, and drive roadmaps through your insights and recommendations\r\nPartner with Product, Engineering, and cross-functional teams to inform, influence, support, and execute product strategy and investment decisions\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor\'s degree in Mathematics, Statistics, a relevant technical field, or equivalent\r\n2+ years of work experience in analytics and data querying languages (e.g. SQL), scripting languages (e.g. Python), and/or statistical/mathematical software (e.g. R)\r\n2+ years of experience solving analytical problems using quantitative approaches, understanding ecosystems, user behaviors & long-term product trends, and leading data-driven projects from definition to execution [including defining metrics, experiment, design, communicating actionable insights]\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nMaster\'s or Ph.D. Degree in a quantitative field\r\nFor those who live in or expect to work from California if hired for this position, please click here for additional information.\r\nAbout Meta\r\nMeta builds technologies that help people connect, find communities, and grow businesses. When Facebook launched in 2004, it changed the way people connect. Apps like Messenger, Instagram and WhatsApp further empowered billions around the world. Now, Meta is moving beyond 2D screens toward immersive experiences like augmented and virtual reality to help build the next evolution in social technology. People who choose to build their careers by building with us at Meta help shape a future that will take us beyond what digital connection makes possible today—beyond the constraints of screens, the limits of distance, and even the rules of physics.\r\n\r\n$115,000/year to $171,000/year + bonus + equity + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base hourly rate, monthly rate, or annual salary only, and do not include bonus, equity or sales incentives, if applicable. In addition to base compensation, Meta offers benefits. Learn more about benefits at Meta. \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nMeta is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, reproductive health decisions, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, genetic information, political views or activity, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. You may view our Equal Employment Opportunity notice here.', '115,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(10, 'Cloud Engineer', 'Microsoft', 'Texas, USA', 'Cloud Engineer at Microsoft, you will shape the future of cloud infrastructure and services that power businesses, developers, and users across our entire ecosystem of products and platforms. By applying your technical skills, cloud expertise, and problem-solving mindset to one of the most advanced cloud environments in the world, you will help define and optimize cloud solutions that drive innovation, scalability, and security. You will collaborate on a wide array of infrastructure and platform challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Engineering, Product, Security, IT, and Operations. You will leverage automation, cloud-native technologies, and best practices to build, deploy, and manage highly available and resilient cloud systems. You will influence cloud strategy, infrastructure investments, and operational best practices while working closely with other teams. By joining Microsoft, you will become part of a world-class cloud engineering community dedicated to professional growth, technical excellence, and career advancement.  \r\n\r\nInfrastructure leadership: You will use cloud technologies to design, build, and optimize scalable, resilient, and secure infrastructure. You will help teams prioritize cloud adoption strategies, set performance benchmarks, and implement best practices for cloud architecture.  \r\n\r\nAutomation and scalability: You will guide teams using cloud automation, infrastructure-as-code (IaC), and DevOps methodologies to improve efficiency and reduce operational overhead. You will employ a diverse toolkit of cloud-native technologies, scripting languages, and monitoring solutions to ensure system reliability.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and influence: You won’t simply manage cloud environments—you will drive innovation and transformation. You will collaborate with engineers, architects, and leadership to design and implement cloud solutions that align with business goals. You will build credibility through structured problem-solving, clear communication, and strategic recommendations.  \r\n\r\nCloud Engineer Responsibilities  \r\nDesign, implement, and maintain scalable, secure, and highly available cloud infrastructure  \r\nDevelop automation and infrastructure-as-code solutions using tools like Terraform, Bicep, or ARM templates  \r\nOptimize cloud performance, cost, and security across Microsoft Azure environments  \r\nManage CI/CD pipelines for cloud deployments and automate operational workflows  \r\nImplement monitoring, logging, and observability solutions to ensure system reliability  \r\nCollaborate with security teams to enforce compliance, governance, and cloud security best practices  \r\nTroubleshoot cloud infrastructure issues, conduct root cause analysis, and implement long-term solutions  \r\nPartner with cross-functional teams to drive cloud strategy, architecture decisions, and operational improvements  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in cloud engineering, DevOps, or site reliability engineering (SRE)  \r\nProficiency in cloud platforms, with a focus on Microsoft Azure  \r\nExperience with automation and scripting (PowerShell, Python, Bash, or similar)  \r\nHands-on experience with CI/CD tools (Azure DevOps, GitHub Actions, Jenkins)  \r\nKnowledge of cloud networking, security best practices, and identity management (Azure Active Directory, IAM policies)  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nCertifications such as Microsoft Certified: Azure Solutions Architect, Azure DevOps Engineer, or equivalent  \r\nExperience with Kubernetes, container orchestration, and microservices architecture  \r\nKnowledge of hybrid cloud and multi-cloud environments (AWS, GCP, or on-prem integration)  \r\n\r\nAbout Microsoft  \r\nMicrosoft empowers businesses, developers, and individuals with industry-leading cloud solutions, cutting-edge technology, and enterprise-grade security. Our mission is to enable digital transformation through scalable, resilient, and innovative cloud infrastructure. With a commitment to automation, performance optimization, and security best practices, we provide world-class cloud computing services that shape the future of technology.  \r\n\r\n$105,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Microsoft offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nMicrosoft is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '105,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(11, 'DevOps Engineer', 'SecureTech', 'Chicago, USA', 'DevOps Engineer at SecureTech, you will shape the future of our security-focused infrastructure and deployment pipelines across our entire suite of cybersecurity solutions. By applying your technical skills, automation expertise, and problem-solving mindset, you will help define and optimize the way we build, test, and deploy secure applications at scale. You will collaborate on a wide array of system and software challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Engineering, Security, IT, Product, and Operations. You will use automation and cloud-based solutions to streamline workflows, enhance system reliability, and drive operational excellence. You will influence infrastructure strategy, security best practices, and deployment processes while working closely with other teams. By joining SecureTech, you will become part of a world-class DevOps community dedicated to continuous learning, innovation, and career growth.  \r\n\r\nInfrastructure leadership: You will use automation and cloud technologies to build scalable and secure infrastructure, optimize deployment pipelines, and enhance system reliability. You will help your partner teams prioritize operational improvements, set performance goals, and understand the infrastructure ecosystem.  \r\n\r\nAutomation and security: You will guide teams using DevOps principles, focusing on automation, configuration management, and security best practices. You will employ a diverse toolkit of scripting, infrastructure-as-code (IaC), and CI/CD methodologies to improve efficiency and reduce risk.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and influence: You won’t simply maintain systems—you will drive innovation in deployment and operations. You will collaborate with engineers, security teams, and leadership to implement best practices, troubleshoot issues, and improve system resilience. You will build credibility through structure and clarity, becoming a trusted strategic partner in the organization.  \r\n\r\nDevOps Engineer Responsibilities  \r\nDesign, build, and maintain secure, scalable, and highly available infrastructure  \r\nDevelop and optimize CI/CD pipelines to automate software delivery and deployments  \r\nImplement monitoring, logging, and alerting solutions to ensure system reliability and performance  \r\nCollaborate with security teams to integrate DevSecOps best practices into infrastructure and deployment workflows  \r\nManage cloud-based infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) and automate provisioning using infrastructure-as-code (Terraform, CloudFormation, or equivalent)  \r\nTroubleshoot production issues, conduct root cause analysis, and implement long-term solutions  \r\nPartner with Engineering, Security, and Operations teams to improve deployment processes and system architecture  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in DevOps, Site Reliability Engineering (SRE), or Cloud Engineering  \r\nProficiency in scripting and automation (Python, Bash, or similar)  \r\nExperience with CI/CD tools (Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, etc.)  \r\nExperience managing cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP) and containerized environments (Docker, Kubernetes)  \r\nStrong understanding of system monitoring, logging, and security best practices  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nExperience with infrastructure-as-code tools (Terraform, CloudFormation, Ansible)  \r\nKnowledge of security frameworks and compliance standards (SOC 2, NIST, ISO 27001)  \r\nExperience with microservices architecture and distributed systems  \r\n\r\nAbout SecureTech  \r\nSecureTech is a leader in cybersecurity solutions, helping businesses protect their data, infrastructure, and digital assets. Our mission is to build secure, scalable, and resilient systems that empower organizations to operate safely in a digital world. With a focus on innovation, automation, and security best practices, we provide cutting-edge solutions that help companies stay ahead of evolving cyber threats.  \r\n\r\n$95,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, equity, or additional incentives, if applicable. SecureTech offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nSecureTech is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '95,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(12, 'Frontend Developer', 'Netflix', 'San Francisco, USA', 'Netflix is one of the world\'s leading entertainment services, with 283 million paid memberships in over 190 countries enjoying TV series, films and games across a wide variety of genres and languages. Members can play, pause and resume watching as much as they want, anytime, anywhere, and can change their plans at any time.\r\n\r\nSenior Frontend Developer\r\n\r\nWho We Are\r\n\r\nNext Games, a Netflix Game Studio, is a Helsinki-based studio dedicated to crafting fans-first interactive experiences that combine the stories from popular movies and shows with engaging game mechanics. Our values, Caring, Courage, and Curiosity, drive our commitment to our players and each other, with a focus on fun gameplay free from the constraints of free-to-play. \r\n\r\nWe celebrate diversity, with dozens of nationalities and a third of our team identifying as women or non-binary. We don\'t seek culture fit, but rather the unique contributions each individual brings to enrich our culture. If you\'re passionate about creating innovative mobile games in a diverse, supportive environment, we\'re eager to hear from you!\r\n\r\nThe Role\r\n\r\nAs a Senior Frontend Developer, you are a crucial contributor to one of our new game initiatives. As an expert in frontend engineering, you deliver complex features with high-quality, extendable, and stable code. You’ll work from our Helsinki office or your Helsinki home with a team that has a hybrid working style.\r\n\r\nThe ideal developer for this role highly values seeing a project through from the start of development into release and onward through live development. They are driven to improve team processes, reactive to the concerns of players and stakeholders across the organization, and able to balance innovation risks and opportunities against release schedules and ambitious project scope.\r\n\r\nResponsibilities\r\n\r\nBuild gameplay features and systems, with a focus on UI-centric gaming experiences\r\nFix issues and maintain the quality of the codebase\r\nTake ownership over features and tasks\r\nProvide input on technical matters\r\nCollaborate with other stakeholders on game ideas, design, gameplay, and features\r\nResolve performance and stability issues\r\nCreate and maintain relevant technical documentation\r\nPreferred Skills and Experience\r\n\r\nBachelor’s Degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Math, or Engineering \r\nExperience in web front-end development\r\nUnderstanding of mobile software platforms (iOS, Android)\r\nExperience in professional, team-based software development with shipped product(s)  and having worked on a live product\r\nStrong knowledge of TypeScript \r\nExcellent problem-solving skills\r\nProactive, self-starter mentality and a can-do attitude\r\nGood communication skills and proficiency in English\r\nThe Team\r\n\r\nWe are prioritizing flexibility and innovation on a new tech stack that will allow us to use dynamic content to meet the needs of a broad audience. Our team comes from a wide range of backgrounds and experiences, and has a fun and open dynamic. \r\n\r\nDoes this sound good to you? Then apply today! \r\n\r\nInclusion is a Netflix value and we strive to host a meaningful interview experience for all candidates. If you want an accommodation/adjustment for a disability or any other reason during the hiring process, please send a request to your recruiting partner.\r\n\r\nWe are an equal-opportunity employer and celebrate diversity, recognizing that diversity builds stronger teams. We approach diversity and inclusion seriously and thoughtfully. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, ancestry, national origin, caste, sex, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity or expression, age, disability, medical condition, pregnancy, genetic makeup, marital status, or military service.', '108,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(13, 'Backend Developer', 'Spotify', 'New York, USA', 'Backend Developer at Spotify, you will shape the future of music streaming and audio experiences, building scalable and efficient backend systems that power our platform for millions of users worldwide. By applying your technical skills, problem-solving abilities, and passion for backend development, you will help define and optimize the services that deliver seamless music, podcasts, and personalized recommendations. You will collaborate on a wide array of engineering and product challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Software Engineering, Data Science, Product, Infrastructure, and Security. You will use cutting-edge backend technologies, distributed systems, and cloud computing to build robust and high-performance services. You will influence system architecture, scalability decisions, and backend best practices while working closely with other teams. By joining Spotify, you will become part of a world-class engineering community dedicated to technical excellence and career growth.  \r\n\r\nSystem architecture and scalability: You will design and build backend services that are scalable, efficient, and optimized for performance. You will help teams prioritize technical improvements, set service-level objectives, and ensure system reliability.  \r\n\r\nBackend development and optimization: You will guide teams using software engineering best practices, focusing on API design, microservices architecture, and database optimization. You will employ a diverse toolkit of programming languages, frameworks, and cloud technologies to develop and maintain services.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and collaboration: You won’t simply write code—you will drive innovation and technical excellence. You will work closely with engineers, product managers, and designers to implement backend solutions that enhance the user experience. You will build credibility through structured problem-solving, clear documentation, and technical leadership.  \r\n\r\nBackend Developer Responsibilities  \r\nDesign, develop, and maintain scalable backend services and APIs that support millions of users  \r\nOptimize system performance, reliability, and scalability using distributed computing and cloud technologies  \r\nCollaborate with frontend developers, data engineers, and product teams to integrate backend services seamlessly  \r\nWrite clean, maintainable, and efficient code using languages such as Java, Python, or Node.js  \r\nImplement monitoring, logging, and alerting to ensure system health and availability  \r\nWork with databases (SQL and NoSQL) to optimize data storage and retrieval  \r\nParticipate in code reviews, architecture discussions, and technical design sessions  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in backend development, software engineering, or cloud-based systems  \r\nProficiency in backend programming languages (Java, Python, Go, or Node.js)  \r\nExperience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure) and containerized environments (Docker, Kubernetes)  \r\nStrong understanding of RESTful APIs, microservices architecture, and database management  \r\nKnowledge of distributed systems, caching, and performance optimization techniques  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nExperience with event-driven architecture and messaging systems (Kafka, RabbitMQ, etc.)  \r\nFamiliarity with DevOps practices and CI/CD pipelines for backend deployment automation  \r\nKnowledge of GraphQL, gRPC, or other modern API technologies  \r\n\r\nAbout Spotify  \r\nSpotify is the world’s leading audio streaming platform, empowering users to discover, enjoy, and share music and podcasts. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving artists the opportunity to reach their fans and listeners the best audio experience possible. With a commitment to innovation, scalability, and data-driven engineering, we continue to push the boundaries of what’s possible in digital music and entertainment.  \r\n\r\n$112,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Spotify offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nSpotify is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '112,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General');
