(14, 'AI Engineer', 'Tesla', 'Austin, USA', 'AI Engineer at Tesla, you will shape the future of artificial intelligence and machine learning solutions that power Tesla’s cutting-edge technologies, including autonomous driving, robotics, and intelligent manufacturing. By applying your expertise in AI, deep learning, and data-driven decision-making, you will help define and optimize AI models that enhance Tesla’s products and services. You will collaborate on a wide array of engineering and AI challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Software Engineering, Autopilot, Hardware, Data Science, and Research. You will work with some of the largest and most complex data sets to build AI systems that drive innovation, efficiency, and automation. You will influence AI strategy, model architecture, and deployment while working closely with other teams. By joining Tesla, you will become part of a world-class AI research and engineering community dedicated to pushing the boundaries of artificial intelligence and technological advancement.  \r\n\r\nAI model development and optimization: You will design and train AI models that improve Tesla’s autonomous driving, manufacturing automation, and energy solutions. You will help teams prioritize AI applications, optimize model performance, and ensure system reliability.  \r\n\r\nMachine learning and data science: You will guide teams using cutting-edge machine learning techniques, neural networks, and data-driven approaches. You will employ a diverse toolkit of AI frameworks, deep learning models, and optimization algorithms to develop intelligent systems.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and collaboration: You won’t simply build AI models—you will drive AI innovation. You will work closely with engineers, researchers, and product teams to implement AI solutions that enhance Tesla’s technology. You will build credibility through structured problem-solving, clear documentation, and technical leadership.  \r\n\r\nAI Engineer Responsibilities  \r\nDevelop and optimize AI models for Tesla’s autonomous driving, robotics, and intelligent manufacturing systems  \r\nApply deep learning, computer vision, and reinforcement learning techniques to enhance Tesla’s AI capabilities  \r\nCollaborate with software engineers, hardware teams, and data scientists to integrate AI models into Tesla’s products  \r\nWork with large-scale data sets to train, test, and deploy machine learning models in real-world environments  \r\nImplement AI algorithms using frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, or JAX  \r\nOptimize AI model efficiency, accuracy, and inference speed for deployment in Tesla’s hardware  \r\nConduct research and stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in artificial intelligence  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, AI, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in AI, machine learning, or deep learning model development  \r\nProficiency in programming languages such as Python, C++, or Java  \r\nExperience with AI frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, or JAX  \r\nStrong understanding of neural networks, deep learning architectures, and computer vision techniques  \r\nExperience working with large-scale data sets, training pipelines, and real-time AI applications  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nMaster’s or Ph.D. in AI, Machine Learning, or a related field  \r\nExperience with reinforcement learning, natural language processing (NLP), or generative AI models  \r\nFamiliarity with autonomous systems, robotics, or embedded AI applications  \r\n\r\nAbout Tesla  \r\nTesla is on a mission to accelerate the world’s transition to sustainable energy through electric vehicles, battery storage, and AI-powered automation. Our AI team plays a crucial role in developing groundbreaking technology for self-driving cars, smart manufacturing, and intelligent energy solutions. By pushing the boundaries of artificial intelligence, we continue to innovate and redefine the future of transportation and automation.  \r\n\r\n$130,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Tesla offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nTesla is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '130,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(15, 'Product Manager', 'Apple', 'California, USA', 'Product Manager at Apple, you will shape the future of innovative products and services that impact millions of users worldwide. By applying your strategic mindset, technical expertise, and deep understanding of user needs, you will help define, develop, and optimize Apple’s next-generation hardware, software, and ecosystem experiences. You will collaborate on a wide array of product and business challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Engineering, Design, Marketing, Sales, Operations, and Finance. You will leverage data, market insights, and customer feedback to drive product vision, strategy, and execution. You will influence product roadmaps, prioritize features, and lead cross-functional teams to deliver world-class experiences. By joining Apple, you will become part of a world-class product management community dedicated to innovation, excellence, and career growth.  \r\n\r\nProduct strategy and vision: You will define the product vision, align teams around a shared strategy, and ensure that Apple continues to deliver groundbreaking experiences that delight users. You will prioritize key features, set measurable goals, and drive execution across teams.  \r\n\r\nMarket research and user insights: You will leverage customer insights, competitive analysis, and industry trends to identify new opportunities and areas for improvement. You will use data-driven decision-making to inform product development and ensure the highest level of quality.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and leadership: You won’t simply manage products—you will inspire teams and lead them to success. You will collaborate with designers, engineers, and executives to build innovative products that drive Apple’s business forward. You will build credibility through structured problem-solving, clear communication, and strategic influence.  \r\n\r\nProduct Manager Responsibilities  \r\nDefine product strategy, roadmap, and key success metrics to ensure Apple delivers best-in-class experiences  \r\nWork closely with cross-functional teams, including Engineering, Design, and Marketing, to develop and launch innovative products  \r\nAnalyze market trends, customer feedback, and competitive insights to drive product improvements  \r\nCollaborate with stakeholders to prioritize features and define requirements for new product initiatives  \r\nEnsure seamless execution of product development from concept to launch, optimizing for quality and user experience  \r\nLead go-to-market strategy, working with marketing and sales teams to drive adoption and engagement  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Business, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in product management, business strategy, or a related field  \r\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills, with experience using data to drive decision-making  \r\nAbility to work cross-functionally with Engineering, Design, and Marketing teams  \r\nExcellent communication and leadership skills, with the ability to influence stakeholders and drive alignment  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nMaster’s degree in Business Administration (MBA) or a technical field  \r\nExperience in consumer electronics, software, or digital services  \r\nFamiliarity with product development methodologies, Agile, and UX design principles  \r\n\r\nAbout Apple  \r\nApple is on a mission to create the world’s most innovative and user-friendly products, from the iPhone and Mac to services like iCloud and Apple Music. Our product managers play a crucial role in shaping the future of technology, ensuring that Apple continues to lead in design, performance, and customer experience. We are committed to pushing the boundaries of what’s possible and delivering products that make a meaningful impact on people’s lives.  \r\n\r\n$140,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Apple offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nApple is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '140,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(16, 'QA Engineer', 'Adobe', 'Seattle, USA', 'QA Engineer at Adobe, you will shape the future of software quality by ensuring that Adobe’s innovative products and services meet the highest standards of reliability, performance, and user experience. By applying your analytical skills, attention to detail, and deep understanding of software testing methodologies, you will help define and implement test strategies for some of the most widely used creative and digital solutions in the world. You will collaborate on a wide array of engineering and product challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Software Development, Product Management, Design, and Customer Support. You will leverage automation, manual testing, and data-driven insights to identify and resolve quality issues early in the development cycle. You will influence test automation frameworks, performance benchmarks, and quality best practices while working closely with engineering teams. By joining Adobe, you will become part of a world-class quality assurance community dedicated to technical excellence and career growth.  \r\n\r\nSoftware quality and testing strategy: You will design and implement comprehensive test plans to ensure product stability, usability, and performance. You will help teams identify potential defects, prioritize bug fixes, and enhance test coverage across platforms.  \r\n\r\nTest automation and performance optimization: You will leverage automation frameworks and scripting languages to streamline testing processes. You will employ a diverse toolkit of software testing methodologies, performance testing tools, and debugging techniques to improve efficiency.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and collaboration: You won’t simply test software—you will drive innovation in quality assurance. You will work closely with developers, product managers, and designers to integrate testing best practices into the software development lifecycle. You will build credibility through structured problem-solving, clear documentation, and proactive communication.  \r\n\r\nQA Engineer Responsibilities  \r\nDevelop and execute test plans and test cases to ensure software quality across Adobe’s products  \r\nDesign, implement, and maintain automated test scripts using frameworks like Selenium, Appium, or JUnit  \r\nCollaborate with development teams to identify, report, and track software defects  \r\nConduct performance, security, and usability testing to optimize product reliability  \r\nAnalyze test results and provide detailed feedback to engineering and product teams  \r\nWork with CI/CD pipelines to integrate automated testing into the development workflow  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in software testing, quality assurance, or test automation  \r\nProficiency in test automation frameworks (Selenium, Appium, JUnit, TestNG) and scripting languages (Python, Java, JavaScript)  \r\nUnderstanding of software development lifecycles, Agile methodologies, and CI/CD pipelines  \r\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nExperience with performance testing tools (JMeter, LoadRunner) and API testing frameworks (Postman, RestAssured)  \r\nFamiliarity with cloud-based testing environments and containerization (Docker, Kubernetes)  \r\nKnowledge of accessibility testing and security testing best practices  \r\n\r\nAbout Adobe  \r\nAdobe is a global leader in digital creativity, providing industry-leading tools such as Photoshop, Illustrator, and Premiere Pro. Our commitment to innovation and quality ensures that millions of users can create, design, and deliver content with ease. Our QA engineers play a vital role in maintaining the reliability and excellence of our software, ensuring that Adobe continues to push the boundaries of digital experiences.  \r\n\r\n$95,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Adobe offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nAdobe is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '95,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(17, 'Marketing Specialist', 'Airbnb', 'San Francisco, USA', 'Marketing Specialist at Airbnb, you will shape the future of travel and hospitality by developing and executing marketing strategies that engage millions of guests and hosts worldwide. By applying your creativity, analytical mindset, and deep understanding of consumer behavior, you will help drive brand awareness, user engagement, and business growth. You will collaborate on a wide array of marketing and business initiatives with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Brand, Growth, Product, Data, Design, and Communications. You will use data-driven insights to craft compelling campaigns, optimize marketing performance, and refine Airbnb’s positioning in the global marketplace. You will influence marketing strategies, campaign execution, and performance measurement while working closely with other teams. By joining Airbnb, you will become part of a world-class marketing community dedicated to creativity, impact, and career growth.  \r\n\r\nMarketing strategy and campaign development: You will help shape Airbnb’s marketing efforts by creating campaigns that resonate with users, attract new guests and hosts, and strengthen Airbnb’s brand. You will support campaign planning, execution, and optimization across multiple channels.  \r\n\r\nData-driven decision-making: You will leverage consumer insights, performance metrics, and market trends to refine marketing strategies. You will employ a diverse toolkit of marketing analytics, A/B testing, and creative storytelling to enhance Airbnb’s marketing effectiveness.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and collaboration: You won’t simply launch campaigns—you will tell stories that inspire. You will work closely with designers, content creators, and data analysts to craft compelling narratives that connect with Airbnb’s global audience. You will build credibility through structured storytelling, clear messaging, and strategic thinking.  \r\n\r\nMarketing Specialist Responsibilities  \r\nDevelop and execute marketing campaigns that drive user engagement, brand awareness, and business growth  \r\nAnalyze consumer trends, campaign performance, and market research to optimize marketing strategies  \r\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams, including Brand, Growth, and Product, to align marketing initiatives with business goals  \r\nManage and optimize marketing channels such as digital advertising, social media, email, and partnerships  \r\nCreate compelling content and messaging that enhances Airbnb’s brand identity and resonates with target audiences  \r\nMonitor campaign success metrics, generate reports, and provide data-driven recommendations for improvement  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, Communications, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in marketing, advertising, or brand management  \r\nProficiency in digital marketing tools, analytics platforms, and content management systems  \r\nStrong analytical skills, with the ability to interpret marketing data and consumer insights  \r\nExcellent communication, storytelling, and project management skills  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nExperience in the travel, hospitality, or tech industry  \r\nFamiliarity with marketing automation platforms, SEO, and paid media strategies  \r\nAbility to work in a fast-paced environment and manage multiple projects simultaneously  \r\n\r\nAbout Airbnb  \r\nAirbnb is on a mission to create a world where anyone can belong anywhere. Through its global platform, Airbnb connects millions of guests with unique accommodations, experiences, and communities in over 220 countries. Our marketing team plays a crucial role in shaping the brand, engaging users, and driving business growth through creative and impactful campaigns.  \r\n\r\n$85,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Airbnb offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nAirbnb is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '85,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(18, 'UX Designer', 'Figma', 'Los Angeles, USA', 'UX Designer at Figma, you will shape the future of design collaboration by crafting intuitive and engaging user experiences that empower designers, developers, and teams worldwide. By applying your design expertise, user-centered mindset, and problem-solving skills, you will help define and enhance Figma’s product suite, making design accessible and efficient for millions of users. You will collaborate on a wide array of product and design challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Product, Engineering, Research, and Marketing. You will use data, user insights, and design best practices to create seamless experiences, improve usability, and drive product innovation. You will influence design strategy, contribute to Figma’s design system, and advocate for user needs while working closely with other teams. By joining Figma, you will become part of a world-class design community dedicated to innovation, impact, and career growth.  \r\n\r\nUser-centered design: You will define and refine user experiences by conducting research, prototyping, and iterating on design solutions. You will ensure that Figma’s tools are intuitive, efficient, and enjoyable for users.  \r\n\r\nCross-functional collaboration: You will work closely with Product Managers, Engineers, and Researchers to bring ideas to life. You will translate user insights and business goals into impactful design solutions that enhance the Figma experience.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and storytelling: You won’t just design interfaces—you will craft meaningful experiences. You will articulate design decisions, advocate for users, and present your work with clarity and confidence. You will build credibility through structured problem-solving and user-first thinking.  \r\n\r\nUX Designer Responsibilities  \r\nDesign and prototype intuitive user experiences for Figma’s product ecosystem  \r\nConduct user research, gather insights, and apply feedback to improve usability and accessibility  \r\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to define product goals, requirements, and design strategies  \r\nContribute to and evolve Figma’s design system to ensure consistency and scalability across products  \r\nValidate design decisions through usability testing, data analysis, and iteration  \r\nAdvocate for user needs and champion best practices in UX and interaction design  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Design, Human-Computer Interaction (HCI), or a related field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in UX/UI design, interaction design, or product design  \r\nProficiency in design tools like Figma, Sketch, or Adobe XD, with a strong understanding of design principles and UX best practices  \r\nExperience with user research, usability testing, and data-driven design decisions  \r\nExcellent communication and problem-solving skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nExperience designing for SaaS, collaboration tools, or productivity software  \r\nKnowledge of front-end development principles (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) to better collaborate with engineers  \r\nFamiliarity with accessibility standards and inclusive design practices  \r\n\r\nAbout Figma  \r\nFigma is redefining how teams design, collaborate, and build together. As a cloud-based design tool, Figma enables seamless real-time collaboration for designers, developers, and stakeholders worldwide. Our UX designers play a critical role in shaping intuitive and powerful tools that empower the global design community to create their best work.  \r\n\r\n$98,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Figma offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nFigma is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '98,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(19, 'Business Analyst', 'IBM', 'New York, USA', 'Business Analyst at IBM, you will shape the future of business solutions by analyzing data, identifying opportunities, and driving strategic initiatives that enhance IBM’s products and services. By applying your analytical skills, business acumen, and problem-solving expertise, you will help define and implement data-driven decisions that impact global operations. You will collaborate on a wide array of business and technology challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Product, Engineering, Finance, Marketing, and Sales. You will use data, insights, and business intelligence tools to optimize processes, improve decision-making, and support organizational growth. You will influence business strategy, contribute to operational efficiencies, and enhance IBM’s market position while working closely with other teams. By joining IBM, you will become part of a world-class analytics community dedicated to innovation, impact, and career growth.  \r\n\r\nBusiness strategy and analysis: You will evaluate business performance, identify trends, and develop strategic recommendations. You will leverage data analytics to assess opportunities, mitigate risks, and improve operations.  \r\n\r\nData-driven decision-making: You will work with large datasets, business intelligence tools, and forecasting models to inform business strategy. You will employ a diverse toolkit of analytical techniques, data visualization, and financial modeling to optimize business processes.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and collaboration: You won’t just analyze numbers—you will tell compelling data-driven stories. You will work closely with key stakeholders to translate insights into actionable strategies and present findings with clarity and confidence.  \r\n\r\nBusiness Analyst Responsibilities  \r\nAnalyze business processes, performance metrics, and market trends to support data-driven decision-making  \r\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to develop and implement strategic business initiatives  \r\nDesign and manage dashboards, reports, and visualizations to monitor key performance indicators (KPIs)  \r\nConduct research and provide recommendations on operational improvements, cost efficiencies, and revenue opportunities  \r\nSupport project management efforts by gathering requirements, documenting processes, and identifying risks  \r\nAssist in forecasting, budgeting, and financial analysis to support business planning  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nBachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, Economics, Data Science, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience  \r\n2+ years of experience in business analysis, data analysis, or consulting  \r\nProficiency in business intelligence tools (Tableau, Power BI), SQL, and Excel for data analysis and reporting  \r\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to interpret complex datasets  \r\nExcellent communication skills, with the ability to present insights to both technical and non-technical audiences  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nExperience with data analytics platforms (Google Analytics, IBM Cognos, or similar)  \r\nKnowledge of financial modeling, forecasting, and process optimization techniques  \r\nFamiliarity with Agile methodologies and project management tools (JIRA, Asana, or Trello)  \r\n\r\nAbout IBM  \r\nIBM is a global technology leader dedicated to driving innovation in AI, cloud computing, and business solutions. By combining cutting-edge technology with deep industry expertise, IBM helps organizations transform and succeed in a rapidly evolving digital landscape. Our business analysts play a crucial role in shaping strategic initiatives, optimizing operations, and delivering data-driven insights that power IBM’s success.  \r\n\r\n$90,000/year + benefits  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. IBM offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nIBM is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '90,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(20, 'IT Support Engineer', 'Dell', 'Boston, USA', 'IT Support Engineer at Dell, you will play a critical role in ensuring the smooth operation of IT systems and infrastructure, supporting employees, and resolving technical issues efficiently. By applying your troubleshooting skills, technical expertise, and customer service mindset, you will help maintain IT stability and enhance user experience. You will collaborate on a wide range of IT and business challenges with cross-functional teams across Engineering, Security, and Operations. You will use problem-solving techniques, system analysis, and network troubleshooting to resolve issues and optimize IT performance. You will influence IT support strategies, contribute to process improvements, and ensure Dell employees have the technical resources they need to succeed. By joining Dell, you will become part of a world-class IT support community focused on innovation, efficiency, and career growth.\r\n\r\nTechnical troubleshooting and support: You will diagnose and resolve hardware, software, and network issues to ensure operational efficiency. You will provide frontline IT support, responding to incidents, troubleshooting problems, and implementing solutions.\r\n\r\nSystem administration and maintenance: You will assist in managing IT infrastructure, maintaining system performance, and implementing security protocols. You will support IT automation efforts and ensure compliance with company policies.\r\n\r\nCommunication and collaboration: You won’t just solve technical problems—you will provide a great user experience. You will work closely with employees and stakeholders to address IT concerns, educate users, and enhance IT support processes.\r\n\r\nIT Support Engineer Responsibilities\r\nProvide technical support and troubleshooting for hardware, software, and network issues\r\nManage IT systems, including operating systems, cloud services, and enterprise applications\r\nAssist with security updates, patch management, and IT compliance efforts\r\nCollaborate with IT teams to implement new technologies and improve existing infrastructure\r\nDocument technical issues, resolutions, and best practices for future reference\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in IT support, system administration, or network troubleshooting\r\nProficiency in Windows, macOS, and Linux operating systems, as well as IT support tools\r\nStrong problem-solving skills and ability to work in a fast-paced environment\r\nExcellent communication and customer service skills\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud)\r\nFamiliarity with IT security best practices and compliance standards\r\nKnowledge of scripting and automation tools (PowerShell, Python, or Bash)\r\n\r\nAbout Dell\r\nDell is a global leader in technology solutions, empowering businesses and individuals with innovative IT products and services. Our IT support team plays a crucial role in maintaining seamless technology operations, ensuring productivity, and supporting employees worldwide.\r\n\r\n$80,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Dell offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nDell is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '80,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(21, 'DevOps Engineer', 'Slack', 'Chicago, USA', 'DevOps Engineer at Slack, you will play a vital role in building and maintaining the infrastructure that powers Slack’s communication platform. By applying your expertise in automation, cloud computing, and system reliability, you will help ensure smooth deployments, high availability, and scalability. You will collaborate on a wide array of engineering and operational challenges with cross-functional teams across Development, Security, and IT. You will use infrastructure as code, monitoring tools, and performance optimization strategies to improve system efficiency and reliability. You will influence DevOps best practices, contribute to process automation, and help Slack deliver seamless collaboration experiences to users worldwide. By joining Slack, you will become part of a world-class engineering community focused on innovation and operational excellence.\r\n\r\nInfrastructure automation and reliability: You will design, implement, and maintain scalable infrastructure using automation tools and cloud platforms. You will work to enhance system performance, reduce downtime, and improve deployment efficiency.\r\n\r\nMonitoring and security: You will ensure system health by implementing monitoring, logging, and security best practices. You will proactively identify potential issues and resolve incidents quickly.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and communication: You won’t just manage infrastructure—you will work closely with engineers to improve DevOps workflows. You will provide guidance on best practices, optimize CI/CD pipelines, and help teams ship code faster.\r\n\r\nDevOps Engineer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and maintain automated deployment pipelines and cloud infrastructure\r\nMonitor system performance, troubleshoot issues, and implement reliability improvements\r\nOptimize and secure cloud-based services using industry best practices\r\nCollaborate with engineering teams to improve software deployment processes\r\nCreate and maintain documentation for infrastructure and DevOps workflows\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in DevOps, cloud engineering, or site reliability engineering\r\nProficiency in cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud) and infrastructure as code (Terraform, Ansible)\r\nExperience with CI/CD tools (Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI) and containerization (Docker, Kubernetes)\r\nStrong scripting skills (Python, Bash, or Go)\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with monitoring and logging tools (Prometheus, Grafana, Splunk)\r\nKnowledge of security best practices in cloud environments\r\nFamiliarity with database management and performance tuning\r\n\r\nAbout Slack\r\nSlack is a leading collaboration platform that transforms how teams communicate and work together. Our DevOps team plays a crucial role in ensuring reliability, scalability, and efficiency, helping Slack deliver a seamless experience to millions of users worldwide.\r\n\r\n$110,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Slack offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and professional development opportunities.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nSlack is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '110,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(22, 'Blockchain Developer', 'CryptoCorp', 'Miami, USA', 'Blockchain Developer at CryptoCorp, you will play a key role in developing, optimizing, and securing blockchain-based applications and smart contracts. By applying your expertise in decentralized technologies, cryptographic security, and distributed systems, you will help shape the future of blockchain solutions. You will collaborate on a wide range of engineering challenges with cross-functional teams across Development, Security, and Product Management. You will use blockchain protocols, smart contract development, and consensus mechanisms to build scalable, secure, and efficient blockchain applications. You will influence blockchain architecture decisions, contribute to protocol enhancements, and drive innovation in the cryptocurrency and decentralized finance (DeFi) space. By joining CryptoCorp, you will become part of a pioneering blockchain development team dedicated to decentralization, security, and technological advancement.\r\n\r\nBlockchain development and optimization: You will design, develop, and deploy smart contracts and blockchain applications, ensuring efficiency, scalability, and security. You will research new blockchain technologies and implement cutting-edge solutions.\r\n\r\nSecurity and cryptographic integrity: You will analyze and improve blockchain security, ensuring the integrity of transactions, smart contracts, and cryptographic protocols.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and innovation: You won’t just write code—you will help shape blockchain strategy. You will work closely with engineers, product managers, and researchers to enhance blockchain infrastructure and create innovative solutions.\r\n\r\nBlockchain Developer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and optimize smart contracts using Solidity, Rust, or similar languages\r\nImplement blockchain protocols and integrate with decentralized applications (dApps)\r\nEnsure security best practices in blockchain development, including vulnerability assessments and auditing\r\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to design and build blockchain-based solutions\r\nResearch and evaluate emerging blockchain technologies for potential integration\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in blockchain development, smart contracts, and cryptographic security\r\nProficiency in blockchain technologies such as Ethereum, Solana, or Hyperledger\r\nExperience with Solidity, Rust, or Go for smart contract development\r\nUnderstanding of decentralized finance (DeFi), consensus mechanisms, and Web3 technologies\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with Layer 2 scaling solutions and cross-chain interoperability\r\nKnowledge of zero-knowledge proofs (ZKPs) and cryptographic security models\r\nFamiliarity with tokenomics and blockchain governance models\r\n\r\nAbout CryptoCorp\r\nCryptoCorp is a leading innovator in blockchain technology, building secure and scalable solutions for decentralized finance, digital assets, and smart contracts. Our blockchain developers play a critical role in advancing the future of decentralized applications and Web3 technology.\r\n\r\n$125,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. CryptoCorp offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, remote work options, and professional development opportunities.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nCryptoCorp is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '125,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(23, 'Network Engineer', 'Cisco', 'San Diego, USA', 'Network Engineer at Cisco, you will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining secure and scalable network solutions that support Cisco’s global operations. By applying your expertise in networking protocols, security best practices, and performance optimization, you will ensure the reliability and efficiency of Cisco’s network infrastructure. You will collaborate with IT, Security, and Engineering teams to develop network architectures that support business objectives. You will use network automation, monitoring tools, and troubleshooting techniques to enhance network performance and prevent downtime. You will influence network design decisions, contribute to security improvements, and optimize Cisco’s enterprise networking environment. By joining Cisco, you will become part of a highly skilled networking community focused on innovation, reliability, and career growth.\r\n\r\nNetwork design and implementation: You will architect and deploy high-performance network solutions, ensuring security, scalability, and efficiency. You will evaluate new networking technologies and recommend best practices for network optimization.\r\n\r\nSecurity and reliability: You will monitor network performance, troubleshoot issues, and implement security protocols to protect against cyber threats and vulnerabilities.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and automation: You won’t just configure networks—you will work with cross-functional teams to automate network operations and improve overall efficiency.\r\n\r\nNetwork Engineer Responsibilities\r\nDesign and deploy enterprise network architectures, including LAN, WAN, and cloud networking solutions\r\nMonitor and troubleshoot network performance, identifying and resolving issues proactively\r\nImplement security measures, including firewalls, VPNs, and intrusion detection systems\r\nOptimize network operations using automation tools such as Ansible and Python\r\nCollaborate with IT and security teams to ensure compliance with networking best practices\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in network engineering, troubleshooting, and security\r\nProficiency in networking protocols (BGP, OSPF, VLANs, VPNs, etc.) and network hardware (routers, switches, firewalls)\r\nExperience with Cisco networking technologies and certification (CCNA, CCNP)\r\nStrong troubleshooting skills and experience with network monitoring tools\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with cloud networking (AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud)\r\nKnowledge of network automation tools (Ansible, Terraform) and scripting languages (Python, Bash)\r\nFamiliarity with SD-WAN and network virtualization technologies\r\n\r\nAbout Cisco\r\nCisco is a global leader in networking and cybersecurity solutions, empowering organizations with cutting-edge technology for secure and efficient communication. Our network engineers play a crucial role in maintaining reliable and scalable network infrastructure that supports Cisco’s worldwide operations.\r\n\r\n$100,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Cisco offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and career development programs.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nCisco is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '100,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(24, 'Game Developer', 'Epic Games', 'North Carolina, USA', 'Game Developer at Epic Games, you will play a critical role in designing, developing, and optimizing immersive gaming experiences that engage millions of players worldwide. By applying your expertise in game development, graphics programming, and real-time rendering, you will help build the next generation of interactive entertainment. You will collaborate with designers, artists, and engineers to create high-quality gameplay mechanics, physics systems, and AI behaviors. You will use game engines, programming languages, and performance optimization techniques to ensure smooth gameplay and visually stunning environments. You will influence game design decisions, contribute to technical innovations, and push the boundaries of interactive entertainment. By joining Epic Games, you will become part of a world-class game development team committed to creativity, innovation, and excellence.\r\n\r\nGame development and innovation: You will design and implement engaging gameplay mechanics, physics simulations, and AI behaviors. You will work on game features that enhance player experience and immersion.\r\n\r\nGraphics and performance optimization: You will ensure smooth performance and high-quality graphics by optimizing rendering pipelines, shaders, and game physics.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and creativity: You won’t just write code—you will work closely with designers, artists, and animators to bring creative visions to life through cutting-edge technology.\r\n\r\nGame Developer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop and implement game mechanics, AI behaviors, and physics systems using game engines (Unreal Engine, Unity)\r\nOptimize game performance and graphics rendering for smooth gameplay across platforms\r\nCollaborate with artists and designers to integrate assets and create interactive environments\r\nWrite clean, efficient, and maintainable code in C++, C#, or similar languages\r\nDebug and troubleshoot gameplay issues, ensuring a seamless player experience\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Game Development, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in game development, graphics programming, or real-time rendering\r\nProficiency in game engines such as Unreal Engine or Unity\r\nStrong programming skills in C++, C#, or similar languages\r\nExperience with AI programming, physics simulations, or multiplayer networking\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with shader programming (HLSL, GLSL) and real-time rendering techniques\r\nFamiliarity with VR/AR development and spatial computing\r\nKnowledge of cross-platform game development for PC, console, and mobile\r\n\r\nAbout Epic Games\r\nEpic Games is a leading game development company known for creating industry-defining experiences such as Fortnite and Unreal Engine. Our game developers work on cutting-edge technology and innovative gameplay mechanics to deliver immersive and engaging experiences to players around the world.\r\n\r\n$120,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Epic Games offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and career development programs.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nEpic Games is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '120,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General');
