(25, 'Technical Writer', 'Oracle', 'Washington, USA', 'Technical Writer at Oracle, you will play a key role in creating clear, concise, and engaging documentation for Oracle’s cutting-edge technologies. By applying your expertise in technical writing, documentation tools, and user experience, you will help engineers, developers, and customers understand complex systems and software products. You will collaborate with product managers, engineers, and UX designers to develop guides, tutorials, and API documentation that enhance usability and adoption. You will use structured authoring, content management systems, and technical communication strategies to produce high-quality documentation. You will influence documentation standards, contribute to knowledge-sharing initiatives, and help Oracle deliver best-in-class user support. By joining Oracle, you will become part of a world-class technical writing community dedicated to clarity, accuracy, and user experience.\r\n\r\nTechnical writing and documentation: You will create and maintain technical documentation, including user guides, API references, and online help content. You will ensure documentation is accurate, accessible, and easy to understand.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and research: You will work closely with engineers, developers, and product managers to gather information and translate complex concepts into clear, structured content.\r\n\r\nContent strategy and improvement: You won’t just write—you will contribute to documentation strategy, improve content organization, and enhance the user experience.\r\n\r\nTechnical Writer Responsibilities\r\nDevelop, edit, and maintain technical documentation for software products, APIs, and enterprise solutions\r\nCollaborate with engineers and product teams to ensure accurate and up-to-date documentation\r\nUse content management systems and structured authoring tools to create and publish documentation\r\nEnsure consistency in style, tone, and terminology across documentation sets\r\nAnalyze user feedback and improve documentation based on audience needs\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in English, Technical Communication, Computer Science, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in technical writing or documentation for software and technology products\r\nProficiency in documentation tools such as MadCap Flare, Confluence, or DITA XML\r\nStrong ability to explain complex technical concepts clearly and concisely\r\nExperience working with engineers, developers, or product managers to gather technical information\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nExperience with API documentation and developer guides\r\nFamiliarity with programming languages such as Python, Java, or SQL\r\nKnowledge of user experience (UX) writing and information architecture\r\n\r\nAbout Oracle\r\nOracle is a global leader in enterprise software, cloud computing, and database management systems. Our technical writers play a crucial role in making Oracle’s products accessible and easy to use for developers, administrators, and business users.\r\n\r\n$85,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. Oracle offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, retirement plans, and career development programs.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nOracle is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '85,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(26, 'HR Specialist', 'LinkedIn', 'San Francisco, USA', 'HR Specialist at LinkedIn, you will play a vital role in developing and implementing human resource strategies that support LinkedIn’s employees and business objectives. By applying your expertise in recruitment, employee relations, and HR policies, you will help shape a positive workplace culture and drive employee engagement. You will collaborate with hiring managers, HR business partners, and leadership to ensure smooth talent acquisition, onboarding, and professional development processes. You will use HR analytics, employee feedback, and industry best practices to enhance workplace policies and employee experience. You will influence HR strategies, contribute to workforce planning initiatives, and drive a culture of inclusion and growth. By joining LinkedIn, you will become part of a world-class HR team dedicated to supporting employees and fostering career development.\r\n\r\nTalent acquisition and employee engagement: You will support recruitment efforts, help onboard new employees, and drive engagement initiatives to create a positive workplace experience.\r\n\r\nHR policies and compliance: You will ensure adherence to company policies and employment regulations while developing HR strategies that align with LinkedIn’s values and goals.\r\n\r\nCollaboration and strategy: You won’t just manage HR tasks—you will work closely with leadership to improve workplace culture, support employee growth, and enhance retention strategies.\r\n\r\nHR Specialist Responsibilities\r\nManage recruitment and onboarding processes, ensuring a seamless experience for new hires\r\nSupport employee relations initiatives, addressing concerns and fostering a positive work environment\r\nDevelop and implement HR policies in compliance with labor laws and company standards\r\nAnalyze HR metrics to improve workforce planning and employee engagement\r\nCollaborate with managers and employees to drive career development initiatives\r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications\r\nBachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience\r\n2+ years of experience in HR, recruitment, or employee relations\r\nStrong knowledge of labor laws, HR policies, and best practices\r\nExcellent interpersonal and communication skills\r\nExperience with HR software and applicant tracking systems\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\nHR certification (PHR, SHRM-CP)\r\nExperience in a tech or corporate environment\r\nKnowledge of diversity, equity, and inclusion (DEI) strategies\r\n\r\nAbout LinkedIn\r\nLinkedIn is the world’s largest professional networking platform, helping professionals connect, learn, and grow their careers. Our HR specialists play a key role in fostering a workplace culture that supports employee success and business growth.\r\n\r\n$75,000/year + benefits\r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include bonuses, stock options, or additional incentives, if applicable. LinkedIn offers competitive benefits, including healthcare, professional development programs, and wellness initiatives.\r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity\r\nLinkedIn is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '75,000', '2025-03-05 03:58:08', 'General'),
(28, 'Cat Grooming Specialist', 'MeowGroom', 'KL, Malaysia', 'Cat Grooming Specialist at MeowGroom, you will shape the future of feline care and grooming experiences we provide across our entire range of premium pet services. By applying your technical skills, attention to detail, and deep understanding of feline behavior, you will help define the grooming standards that ensure the comfort, hygiene, and well-being of cats in our care. You will collaborate on a wide array of grooming and customer service challenges with a diverse set of cross-functional partners across Grooming, Customer Experience, Marketing, Operations, and Veterinary Support. You will use your expertise in grooming techniques and feline handling to ensure that every cat receives top-tier care in a stress-free environment. You will influence grooming best practices and service innovation with your insights, be focused on impact, and collaborate with other teams. By joining MeowGroom, you will become part of a world-class pet care community dedicated to skill development and career growth in the pet grooming industry.  \r\n\r\nGrooming leadership: You will use your knowledge of feline grooming to shape service offerings, identify new opportunities, address upcoming challenges, and ensure the grooming experience brings value to both cats and their owners. You will help prioritize service improvements, set quality standards, and ensure our grooming techniques are both safe and effective.  \r\n\r\nFeline expertise: You will guide teams using knowledge and insights into feline grooming. You will focus on understanding different coat types, skin conditions, and temperament-based grooming approaches. You will employ a diverse toolkit of grooming methods, including bathing, brushing, trimming, de-matting, and breed-specific styling.  \r\n\r\nCommunication and influence: You won\'t simply groom cats—you will create an unparalleled customer experience. You will educate cat owners on best practices for feline hygiene and coat maintenance, ensuring that every visit leaves both the cat and the owner satisfied. You will build trust through clear explanations, gentle handling, and expert recommendations.  \r\n\r\nCat Grooming Specialist Responsibilities  \r\nWork with cats of all breeds and temperaments to provide a stress-free grooming experience  \r\nApply technical expertise in bathing, brushing, de-shedding, trimming, and styling  \r\nIdentify and assess skin and coat conditions, providing recommendations for care and maintenance  \r\nEnsure the safety and well-being of all feline clients during grooming sessions  \r\nPartner with the Customer Service and Operations teams to enhance the overall client experience  \r\nMaintain a clean, organized, and sanitary grooming environment  \r\nEducate cat owners on post-grooming care and feline hygiene best practices  \r\n\r\nMinimum Qualifications  \r\nCertification in Pet Grooming or equivalent hands-on experience in feline grooming  \r\n2+ years of experience in a grooming salon, veterinary clinic, or pet care facility  \r\nStrong understanding of feline behavior and handling techniques  \r\nAbility to work with grooming tools such as clippers, shears, and de-matting combs  \r\nPassion for cats and commitment to providing top-tier grooming services  \r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications  \r\nAdvanced training in feline grooming techniques or specialized certifications  \r\nExperience working with difficult or anxious cats in a grooming setting  \r\nKnowledge of pet-safe grooming products and feline dermatology  \r\n\r\nAbout MeowGroom  \r\nMeowGroom is dedicated to providing luxury grooming experiences tailored to the unique needs of every cat. Our expert groomers use gentle handling techniques, high-quality products, and industry-leading grooming practices to ensure every feline client receives top-notch care. We believe in enhancing the lives of cats through stress-free, professional grooming services that prioritize comfort, hygiene, and well-being.  \r\n\r\n$12,000/year + potential bonuses  \r\n\r\nIndividual compensation is determined by skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Compensation details listed in this posting reflect the base annual salary only and do not include potential bonuses or incentives, if applicable. In addition to base compensation, MeowGroom offers training and career development opportunities.  \r\n\r\nEqual Employment Opportunity  \r\nMeowGroom is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, or any other legally protected status.', '12,000', '2025-03-05 20:18:00', 'Pets');

